Aetacarus elanoides
sp. n. differs from other described species by the following combination of features: in both sexes, length of si greater than distance separating bases of si (shorter in
A. andrei
), solenidion 1 present on genu III (absent in
A. leptotrichus
); in male, terminal membranes about as wide at base as they are long (conspicuously constricted at base in
A. eurychaetus , hyalothrix , milvi , phylloproctus , puylaerti
), h1 slightly spatulate (strongly falcate in
A . phylloproctus
, lanceolate in
avicedae
and
eurychaetus
), setae g well anterior to genital papillae (between genital papillae in
A. laurencei
); in females, e2 with unique spatulate­mucronate shape shown by no other named species (most similarly shaped in
A. eurychaetus
, but in this species surface of e2 has strongly faceted surface decorations), h1 thick and spine­like (hair­like in
A. eurychaetus , phylloproctus , puylaerti
).
